<br>
To people that are organizing raids there are a few things that you need to think about.<br>
<br>
- Time for the raid.  A weekday raid may not be well attended vs a weekend raid.  A day raid may not be as good as a night raid.  Some people are in the east coast some people in the west coast.  I am fairly confident that majority of people in one of the guilds in the Federation are in Hawaii.  I have found that most raids held on a weekend night get better attendance.  If the Federation creates a members list, maybe they can add a time zone and/or best game times to it.<br>
<br>
- Transportation to the raid.  If you are planning a raid try to get a few druids or wizards to port people to the raid.  I see a lot of raids that say find your own way there.  This is not always possible.  It can take along time to get a port or just move from one area to another.  Many people do not have the time to do this and will just hunt in the area they are in then spend the hour or two to move.  <br>
<br>
- PR for the raid.  Try and build up the raid.  Why do you want to raid this zone?  What can others get out of the zone?  Things of this nature.  Some people will not research a zone so have no clue what the zone can give them.<br>
<br>
Just some thoughts.<br>
<br>
Hey Kankersore...I am hanging in Velious and would love to see any raids in those zones.<br>
<br>
Bendi -- Dont give up just yet.  You have done a great job communicating the raids you have put together.  The eagerness and enthusiasm you bring to the Federation are needed, dont let it slip away.  People will come to raids when they can.<br>
<br>
And I will just through this in for fun...Bendi and Warriousalexis, you both give great reasons why there should be some more thought into consolidating the Federation into one guild.  You can not just get in game and do a guildsay and have the entire Federation here what you have to say.  You must remember that the Federation is made up of 8 different guilds with different goals.<br>
<br>
And peace will come to the land after I have laid all my foes to rest.<br>
<br>
Fulton Tyr'Nor<br>
